<br> <br>
Competition is what drives increases in productivity and wealth. If this weren't the case, you'd be in favor of monopolies. You've regurgitated something you heard online, but I don't think you even considered applying it to yourself to question what you might believe. I'd encourage you to go live in a communist country as it might be enough of a shock for you to realize that it isn't going to work. Everyone else here is at least wise enough to learn from the mistakes of the other countries that tried and failed and have no desire to burn ourselves on that same stove for your sake.</div>
