"certified"???? We don't care if some authority wipes their ass on a certificate, we care about the actual data going in and out not being malicious or subject to eavesdropping. Don't believe me? When's the last time <i>you</i> validated the TLS certs used as a regular part of your browsing?</p><p><div class="quote"><p>Your potable line ISP and the customer are responsible (financially) for every packet put on the line.</p></div><p>
Then it would be avoided like the plague, and Congress would be paid to create exceptions or loopholes for liability. No profit seeking business is going to use it unless forced, and with the recent SCOTUS decisi<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
